req - 3gm ram
1. Open Termux on your Android device.
    


pkg update -y && pkg upgrade -y
2. Update and upgrade the packages by running the following command:
pkg install wget qemu-system-x86-64-headless qemu-utils -y
3. Create a seperate directory:
`mkdir alpine && cd alpine`

4. Download Alpine Linux (virt optimized) ISO:
# https://www.alpinelinux.org/downloads/
wget -O alpine.iso https://dl-cdn.alpinelinux.org/alpine/v3.22/releases/x86_64/alpine-virt-3.22.1-x86_64.iso

6. Create disk (note it won't actually take 15GB of space, more like 500-600MB):

qemu-img create -f qcow2 alpine.qcow2 15G

7. Boot it up: Here we're using 1024MB of memory and 2 cpus

qemu-system-x86_64 -machine q35 -m 1024 -smp cpus=2 -cpu qemu64 -drive if=pflash,format=raw,read-only=on,file=$PREFIX/share/qemu/edk2-x86_64-code.fd -netdev user,id=n1,dns=8.8.8.8,hostfwd=tcp::2222-:22 -device virtio-net,netdev=n1 -cdrom alpine.iso -nographic alpine.img

or

qemu-system-x86_64 -m 512 -netdev user,id=n1,hostfwd=tcp::2222-:22 -device virtio-net,netdev=n1  -cdrom alpine.iso -nographic alpine.qcow2

you can get number of useable cpus using `nproc` and total memory using `free -m | grep -oP '\d+' | head -n 1`


8. Login with username `root` (no password)

apk update

apk add docker

service docker start
service docker status

poweroff

echo "qemu-system-x86_64 -m 512 -netdev user,id=n1,hostfwd=tcp::2222-:22 -device virtio-net,netdev=n1 -nographic alpine.qcow2" >> ~/alpine/run_qemu.sh

chmod +x run_qemu.sh

bash run_qemu.sh

service docker start
rc-update add docker
service docker status
